						<summary>

						<p>Pillar (No. 1) on the tank-bund.</p>						

						<p>10th century A.D. </p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record states that Ēṟegāri who bore the title Nanniyagōva (protector of truth) among others, was holding the office of <hi rend="italic">Nāḻ-gāvuṇḍa</hi> for Bāḍa division. The characters are of about 10th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
